      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "I think this is a reasonable enough escape hatch. Given that we only have 1 currently, requiring a `// FOO` rather than a `/* FOO */` seems ok to me.\r\n\r\nI don't see how we could do it as a clang-tidy plugin unfortunately. Its preprocessor stuff kinda sucks, and I believe we'd also have to keep a hard-coded list because any actual `bitcoin-config.h` would be guaranteed to leave _some_ things undef'd. Hmm, I suppose the plugin itself could read the `.h.in` for each invocation. That's pretty ugly though :(",
